dena its evolutionary history and challenge to the global game market events at stanford dena its evolutionary history and challenge to the global game market facebook twitter email print add to calendar mr dai watanabe president and ceo of dena global inc describes the rapid growth evolution of business models and current efforts toward globalization of the $1.4 billion revenue japanese parent company dena producer of the mobage mobile social gaming platform which has over 30 million users and 1000 games in the japan market mobage's revenue per user is 30x that of facebook and 15x in comparison to zynga having recently created mobage china and bought the us gaming company ngmoco for $300 m dena is now taking on the challenges of global expansion mr watanabe will also discuss new developments in mobile social games and directions of mobile gaming markets in general session in the us asia technology management center series of public talks on mobile internet businesses and technologies in asia when thursday november 3 2011 4 15 pm approximate duration of 1.25 hour s where skilling auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags lecture reading international engineering sponsor presented by the us asia technology management center school of engineering with support from altus technologies and olympus corporation contact 650 724 0096 siejeny stanford edu admission open to all at no charge light refreshments afterward permalink http events stanford edu events 296 29631 more info last modified october 27 2011
